The Address Book Tutorial shows how to put together a simple yet
fully-functioning GUI application. The tutorial chapters can be found in the
Qt documentation, which can be viewed using Qt Assistant or a Web browser.

The tutorial is also available online at

http://qt-project.org/doc/qt-5.0/qtwidgets/tutorials-addressbook.html

This is a D/Qt port of the original C++ tutorial, using DQt bindings.

Building with DUB (all parts):

    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part1
    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part2
    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part3
    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part4
    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part5
    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part6
    dub build --compiler=ldc2 :part7

Or build a single part from its directory:

    cd part1 && dub build --compiler=ldc2

Binaries are placed in partN/bin/.
